msgs.Content: here come the Strong Formal Elephants, who will now be introduced
Good Day, Sirs and Ladies! I am Shoomp!
Hello Ladies and Gentle-phants, I am Midee, the elephants.
My vocabulary is sublime, for I must always rhyme.
Ahhh that's right, I had forgotten. You and your kind speak Rhymish
*lifts a tea cup to their excellence*
I'm glad you all got my invitation
It's good to discuss these grave things with those of my kind
Oh no! What is the woe?
The suspense is great? What is the wait?
I'm afraid that the Sadness™ that we have heard about is now approaching the outskirts of our land
Oh dear! Not the sadness I  fear!
I have received word that as we speak, the dank monkey monks are having their temples infected with the Sadness™
*trumpet call to signal his Seeing Eye Elephant*
They no longer enjoy the solemnity of memes in their sacred place of worship!
Not the Monkey Monks! Could they not ward it off with their great amounts of funk?
Although I, a very Formal Elephant, do not agree with such religious memery, my Formal heart goes out to these monkey monks
But we all know how they are... *shakes head solemnly*
Of course they are doing their best, but this still fills me with so much  stress!
It is I, Calypso the Bear! I am here because I heard the seein eye elefant is here
Ah, Calypso! How does it go?
*gives calypso a kiwi as a symbol of diplomacy*
Oi alweys cood cant on yu for eh wehm weelcom
But Oi wented to knoaw whet thu seein oi eelefent  hed to sey
BUNGY THIS IS NOT THE TIME FOR IMFORMALITY

and sadness will soon come upon us too

time to form a party to scout out the temple
yeh thets all weel end gud  but yu sed somethun ehbaot feeh?
yes if we do not Act Now
Fear is here! I didn't know it was already so near!
What do we do now, see-er?
dud yu brung theh chups end gueck cuz?
Is fear a friend? I don't know what message to send!
I need to go sort out my thoughts. Come and get me if anyone brings brauts.
You broke your formal vow of formal silence!
Ah, I am glad. I feared fear was allied with sad.
I'm too afraid to remain silent any longer
But fear is here and that means the end is near
this is an abomination that must be stopped
What do you suggest, we "get rid of" our guest?
I thought fear was our friend, and now he  must end?
agreed but we must do something
We must excuses to suggest that our gathering is ending
such as "Oh it's getting late. I think we're all tired"
calypso I do, believe, you're due, to leave, for your BUSUNESS TRIP is that correct
That is the PROPER thing to do

it was a PLEASURE SEEING YOU AGAIN
Goodbye! Too bad you have to fly!
now we have to go to the temple
fear can join us but only if they behave properly
To the Monks! We shall help them with our trunks!
How do we get there? Does anyone know where?
oh no but what if we have to have an ETIQUETTE MONTAGE for fear
Oh! Hmm... Fear.. isn't it getting late? Don't you have somewhere to be?
But fear isn't a strong elephant?
*Quietly* I thought fear was staying here?
I don't know. I'm afraid I can't tell
he will come. we'll train him and he'll be a great assett
We need a test, to make sure he's the best!
And so they go to the Temple Bemple
Fear has brought us near! Can I hear a Here Here?!
AAAAAAAA I AM FILLED WITH FEAR! WE ARE TOO NEAR!
*crawls out of Mindee* YES! We are!
everything is becoming bad what are we supposed to do
Ham Here Here, can you save me, my friends, and Fear?!
it's time for fear to accomplish its purpose
*grabs fear and attempts to chuff him right into the sadness*
DON'T FEED FEAR TO SADNESS, THAT IS BADNESS!!
I SUGGEST, YOU DON'T FEED MONSTERS OUR GUESTS!
But it was too late. Fear was already flying through the air.
WE ARE FORMAL, AND THAT IS NOT NORMAL!!!!
*flames sparking from it's oozing, pulpy mass*

FEAR! TELELPORT AWAY, SO YOU ARE NOT NEAR!!
*gurgling noises as he gets absorbed by flame and goo*
*REACHES WITHIN SADNESS, AND GRABS FEAR WITH MY TRUNK*

I did what I had to do
OUR GUEST IS DEAD! FEEL THE GUILT IN YOUR HEAD!
AGH AGH *coughing and  gurgling and sputtering* AGGHHAAAH

AI MANAGED TO GET OUT ALIVE
BUT COULD NOT GET OUT FEAR, NOT MATTER HOVE I DID STRIVE

*turning to Bungy* You took the proper course of action.
A silence fell on our heroes(?)
Sadness, can you hear me? I think you may have been misunderstood, you see.
Bungy, is a villain, I think. His sanity may be teetering on the brink.
*all neighing ferociously at once* THE FHORSES OF EVIL!!!!
You shouldve listened to me Mindee!

*returns as a beautiful ghost* your quest is only beginning

I THINK WE MUST SCURRY! WE SHOULD LEAVE IN A HURRY!!
SHOOMP, YOU TRASH! I'LL TURN YOU INTO HAS!!

it is no time to fight. you must _sssttttooop himmmm_
I'LL TALK WITH YOU LATER! THE TOWN MUST BE SAVED,  YOU HATER

Ham Here Here, I am glad you are still near.
You have great courage, and we need you to encourage.
Our spirits are down. Please help us stop our frowns.
*slips in sadness sludge and begins melting*
*as she melts into oblivion* WHAT AN IMPROPER WAY TO GOOOOOOOOO......
BUT I MUST NOT GET DOWN! I MUST SAVE THE TOWN!
HAM HERE HERE! HELP ME, YOU HEAR?

Look. I wish I could help-well...that's not true-BUT

*trumpets with annoyance, and runs to the beyblade *

I hope this person is heroic,
Hello? Anyone there? If there is, then where?
Midee, in seek of a hero. Are you one, or are you a zero?

Now if you'll excuse me, I have things to do. No one believes that tale and neither should you.

Set sadness alight, and while it burned, tossed my friend fear to it, without even a fight!
*drops down behind Mindee from a hole in the ceiling*
is that all the screaming I heard?
EEPS! You gave me the creeps! And yes, that's my guess.
For the closest city, with the Elephant riding them laughing all giddy.

Let me grab some things and then lets go
do not go my child it is too dangerous *RIBBIT*
All Froge have foretold this tragic tail *RIBBIT*

🎶 but I warn u do not go or u will meet a bad fate worse than death

Maybe someone can tell us what happened

Hold on! I think I see *cough*_someone_ *cough* pinned under the wreckage of this building.

You lift up the beams with your trunk and I'll pull him out!
Yes! Don't worry, we'll do our best!

tell my wife and child I love them
